comments.body:
Some more additional info:

1. I need to manually set the execution policy when importing PSDesiredStateConfiguration or I get the "cannot be loaded because the execution of scripts is disabled on this system." message.

2. When running the following block I get the same error as in https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/2902. 
```
using (PowerShell ps = PowerShell.Create())
{
	try
	{
		ps.AddScript("Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted -Scope Process -Force");
		ps.AddScript("Import-Module PSDesiredStateConfiguration");
		ps.AddScript("Get-DscResource");
		var test = ps.Invoke();
	}
	catch (Exception e)
	{
		Console.WriteLine(e.Message);
	}
}
```
`Cannot find type [Microsoft.PowerShell.DesiredStateConfiguration.DscResourceInfo]: verify that the assembly containing this type is loaded.`
